![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/cdb2128b-ca30-4502-ab78-616c858806d9/wwe-drew-mcintyre-summerslam2.jpg)

The wrestling world is abuzz with updates on McIntyre's future with the company following the announcement that he has signed a new contract with WWE.

According to PWInsider, McIntyre will take a necessary recovery period off of TV due to a badly hyperextended elbow. Despite the setback, McIntyre powered through WWE's UK Tour, earning admiration and respect from both fans and officials.

The big news, however, revolves around McIntyre's contract negotiations. After months of speculation, WWE and McIntyre have finally reached an agreement. The negotiation process culminated just 2-3 days ago, reports PWInsider.

The video that The Rock posted on his Instagram was actually shot well in advance so WWE had something they could put out once they finalized negotiations, but discussions weren't concluded until just a few days ago.

Fightful reported that McIntyre's new deal with WWE is a multi-year agreement, signaling a long-term commitment from both the wrestler and the company. The report also emphasizes the mutual satisfaction expressed by both parties, indicating a promising future ahead.

As McIntyre continues his recovery and prepares for his return to the squared circle, fans eagerly anticipate the next chapter in his illustrious career.